{NORTH opens 2\C with her balanced 22 points.

SOUTH has 8 points AND a 5-card \S suit. This is strong enough for a positive response, so 
he bids 2\S.

NORTH completes the description of her hand by saying 2NT.

SOUTH does NOT rebid the \Ss; his first bid already promised a 5-card suit. He just 
bids 3NT.}

